      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SNITZEL DANCER (2) was in the market but performed a little below par last start over 1400m at Warwick Farm. Fitter for two runs back from a spell, drops back in grade, and wears blinkers for the first time. Watch for a much better run. CRIMSON MISS (5) returned from a 40-day let-up with an eye-catching third over 1300m at Goulburn last time out. That run should top her off nicely for the extra furlong today. Looms as the obvious danger. CANADIAN FLING (7) backs up eight days after a meek performance over today's journey at Goulburn. The soft conditions may be to blame for that defeat, so if this track is in good order she can turn things around. The sparingly raced DYNAST KING (3) has been freshened up and has the ability to test this field.",
